include/osdep_service_linux.h: follow the timer API renames

Our kernel (6.18.33) has fully removed the old `from_timer()` macro and
`del_timer_sync()` function -- they were renamed to `timer_container_of()`
and `timer_delete_sync()` respectively as part of the kernel's timer
subsystem cleanup, with the old names dropped entirely by this point
(include/linux/timer.h in our tree defines only the new names). Without
this, both call sites in this driver's OS-abstraction header fail:

    osdep_service_linux.h:359:26: error: implicit declaration of function
    'from_timer'; did you mean 'mod_timer'?
    osdep_service_linux.h:388:23: error: implicit declaration of function
    'del_timer_sync'; did you mean 'dev_mc_sync'?

Pure rename, no behavior change. (Note: the identifier `from_timer` also
appears, unrelated, as a plain boolean parameter/variable name throughout
core/rtw_mlme_ext.c -- those are NOT this macro and are untouched by this
patch; grep confirms the macro is invoked, as a function-like call, at
exactly this one call site in the whole driver tree.)

P3.1, PLAN.md §4.1 class E. Not sent upstream (no CI/maintainer contact
established for this pin).

diff --git a/include/osdep_service_linux.h b/include/osdep_service_linux.h
--- a/include/osdep_service_linux.h
+++ b/include/osdep_service_linux.h
@@ -356,7 +356,7 @@
 #endif
 {
 #if (LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(4, 14, 0))
-	_timer *ptimer = from_timer(ptimer, in_timer, timer);
+	_timer *ptimer = timer_container_of(ptimer, in_timer, timer);
 #else
 	_timer *ptimer = (_timer *)cntx;
 #endif
@@ -385,7 +385,7 @@

 __inline static void _cancel_timer(_timer *ptimer, u8 *bcancelled)
 {
-	*bcancelled = del_timer_sync(&ptimer->timer) == 1 ? 1 : 0;
+	*bcancelled = timer_delete_sync(&ptimer->timer) == 1 ? 1 : 0;
 }

 static inline void _init_workitem(_workitem *pwork, void *pfunc, void *cntx)
